ng position for pre and post doctoral researchers that cisac plans to establish in honor of william perry the 19th us secretary of defense and former cisac co director perry fellows will reside at cisac for a year of policy relevant research on international security issues the will join other distinguished scientists social scientists and engineers who work together on security problems that cannot be solved within any single field of study cisac researchers address overlapping issues in nuclear weapons policy and nuclear proliferation regional tensions biosecurity homeland security and effective global engagement the deadline for applications is feb 1 2009 william j perry fellowship in international security fellowship for postdoctoral scholars professionals international scholars not accepting applications at this time search cisac news everything news of interest we are accepting applications for our 2012 2013 fellowship programs december 15 2011 cisac fsi stanford announcement lynn eden david holloway and william perry a world free of nuclear weapons april 7 2011 announcement william perry testifies before senate foreign relations committee april 29 2010 in the news new un resolution aims at nuclear free world september 24 2009 cisac fsi stanford in the news william perry on north korea march 16 2009 in the news first william j perry international security fellowship endowed at cisac december 17 2007 press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
